Fufu powder is a white fermented carbohydrate food processed from cassava roots. This is odourless, which is a complete opposite of the traditional wet fufu. It is very low in cyanide content, with less than 10pm. Required raw materials: The major raw material is cassava roots: Market prospects: Fufu powder is a staple food consumed in every part of Nigeria and the West African sub-region. Apart from the fertile Nigerian market, fufu powder can be exported not only to other parts of the country, but also to Europe and America. Process description: Required machineries Note that the estimated cost of investment is from N850,000 and above depending on the capacity you wish to install. Profitability Return on investment            31% Return on equity                      65% Payback period                         2 years Break-even point                     55.1%